I have added information about Jain's Meteorite collection. Please don't delete this edit but review and make changes if you think it needs them, like [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Naveen_Jain&type=revision&diff=824647829&oldid=824645212 here]. Following this [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=User_talk%3ATrufflegoblin&type=revision&diff=828463145&oldid=826050240 discussion] with Ronz, which underlines the unbiased approach we both have to this page. I recall adding similar information to an edit that was reverted, but here there is very basic information about the meteorite collection only... I consider information about what some could consider to be an eccentric and outrageously expensive hobby to be an noteworthy addition to a balanced and neutral biography.

Following this [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=User_talk%3ATrufflegoblin&type=revision&diff=828280996&oldid=828278284 discussion] with Ronz, which underlines the unbiased approach we both have to this page. it would be great if people could make relevant neutral changes to this content. All sources I have used appear on the Notability Review that someone recently added to the [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Talk:Naveen_Jain talkpage]. This would be very helpful in continuing to develop this balanced and neutral biography.
